THE PILOT LEFT THE HELICOPTER UNATTENDED WITH THE ENGINE AT IDLE AND 
THE ROTOR SYSTEM DISENGAGED.  WHILE UNATTENDED, THE ENGINE 
ACCELERATED, AND THE ROTOR SYSTEM DRIVE BELTS ENGAGED.  THE UNPILOTED 
HELICOPTER MOVED ACROSS THE GROUND, STRUCK A POLE AND WAS 
SUBSTANTIALLY DAMAGED.  POST-CRASH INSPECTION REVEALED THE COLLECTIVE 
IN THE FULL UP POSITION. 
inadvertant engagement of the rotor drive system, while the helicopter had been left 
unattended by the pilot. 
